The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for generating human-like stories from images, incorporating natural language image descriptions. This involves both computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed method, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and statistical analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of generating coherent and contextually relevant stories.
